<p>
<strong>Contract offered</strong>: Full time contractor</p>
<p>
<strong>Location</strong>: Chamb&eacute;ry, France or telecommute. We&rsquo;re very used to remote collaboration since the dev team is working remotely already, we&rsquo;ll consider any location in a European-ish timezone.</p>
<p>
<strong>Experience required</strong>: Advanced, 3+ years</p>
<p>
<strong>Language</strong>: English is required, we&rsquo;re a french company but all communication is in english, some of our developers / designers don&rsquo;t even speak french&nbsp;<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<h1>
The Job</h1>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for an experienced Ruby on Rails developer to join our dev team.</p>
<p>
We&rsquo;re looking for the following skills:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Proficient with Ruby (1.9.3) on Rails (3.2)</li>
<li>
Good knowledge of Relational Databases i.e. Postgresql and SQL</li>
<li>
Used to TDD workflow : rspec, JSLint, capybara, Jenkins CI</li>
<li>
Experienced with scaling applications: code optimization, caching with Varnish/Redis</li>
<li>
Familiar with Front-End techniques: Javascript/jQuery, HAML/SASS, liquid</li>
<li>
EC2 / S3</li>
<li>
Capistrano or Puppet experience is a plus</li>
</ul>
<p>
Our favorite tools: Github, New Relic, Airbrake, Pivotal Tracker, Basecamp, Campfire</p>
<p>
The challenges you will face include:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Build new features that will be used by 100 000 stores</li>
<li>
Performance analysis and optimization on an application serving 11 million pages per month</li>
<li>
Integrate our application with other services</li>
<li>
A strong focus on API and mobile</li>
</ul>
<p>
You will be involved in architecture and implementation of our application, from the technical and functional perspective.</p>
<p>
The team is small so you get to really make an impact:</p>
<ul>
<li>
Fast release cycles (2 weeks)</li>
<li>
We work with pull requests for everything</li>
<li>
You will endorse the rotating &ldquo;Release Master&rdquo; responsibility as soon as you&rsquo;ll be ready</li>
<li>
Your opinion on tech and architecture choices is welcome, don&rsquo;t hesitate to speak your mind!<br />
&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<h1>
The Company</h1>
<p>
Leadformance is a software company founded in 2007. We are a team of 27 located in Paris and Chamb&eacute;ry (France), with a dev team working remotely.</p>
<p>
We are the european leader in Web to Store solutions with 120 clients like L&rsquo;Or&eacute;al, Panasonic, LG, Fendi, Tag Heuer, Orange, Darty, 1-2-3 Etam, Subaru, Optical Center, Quiksilver, Castorama, Havas Voyages&hellip;</p>
<p>
Our application is used by 100 000 stores in more than 100 countries.</p>
<p>
In 2010 we won the Paris ecommerce innovation award. In 2011 the PagesJaunes group invested in the company.<br />
&nbsp;</p>
<h1>
The Location</h1>
<p>
Even if we choose to collaborate remotely in the beginning, you&rsquo;ll probably decide to relocate once you get the chance to visit the company headquarters!</p>
<p>
Our Chamb&eacute;ry office is located just several miles away from the world&rsquo;s best ski resorts (Courchevel, Meribel, Val d&rsquo;Is&egrave;re...) and 15 minutes from the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lac_du_Bourget" target="_blank">biggest lake in France</a>.</p>
<p>
The area is well connected, with 2 international airports (Lyon and Geneva) at 1h drive from the office.</p>
